So as you all have heard, Brian Roberts + Yankees = Bad News. But I thought I would share this with you all, cause I know how much you just LOVE hearing about him..

 

It was hard to watch, especially for Roberts' teammates. Shortstop Miguel Tejada has grown close to Roberts and they were both starters in the All-Star Game in July.

"After I see Brian going go down like that, my game went down, I couldn't concentrate," he said. "The only thing I could think about is what happened to Brian. He is the last guy I want to see going down like that. He worked hard to be the player he is. He never complains about anything."

Tejada said he called home after the game and his 5-year-old daughter Alexa began crying when he told her the news about Roberts.

"She loves Brian Roberts so much," Tejada said. "I really feel sorry for him. I hope everything is going good for him."

 

I do too. I love Brian Roberts SO much.. and when I go to fanfest (praying) I'm going to kiss it and make it all better for him (if he's there)... (again praying).

Okay, so yesterday me and Cait left for B-more at like 1ish. We got there at like 2:30 and spent a half hour trying to find a parking garage in B-more that wasn't closed or shady.. and after being eye raped by at least 4 different mexicans, we made it to our parking garage. It was perfect, straight down 4 blocks from the stadium, right beside McDonald's, and 2 blocks from SUBWAY. That's where we went first. It was about 3 when we ate lunch (ridiculous I know.. lol) but it wasn't that bad for an inner-city Baltimore fast-food restaurant, it didn't smell anything like the McDonald's. It was VERY clean and the people were VERY nice. I was impressed. After we ate, we headed to the Gallery to waste some time and do some shopping (because the shops there are the best, like, ever). We went in Forever 21, payless (i <3 payless.. lol), Claire's (there was a 40-yr old gay guy working there who kept smelling cookies.. weird), Wet Seal (my new place of obsession), and lots of other places but all I bought were these orange beads from Claire's cause I needed some orange jewelry for the game. Then we went to Starbucks and saw a HOTTIE. and I'm talkign HOTTIE. so cait took a pic of him with her phone, so stalkerish I know.. but I'm telling you. HOT-TIE. So we headed back to the car to get changed.. after almost being stampeded by a guy with a big cart yelling at us to get out of the way, we're like HELLO its a freaking sidewalk, we're not going to get out of the way! So we got back to the car, changed, sat in the air for a few minutes, then headed to the ballpark. We got some stares as we walked the 4 blocks, but oh well.
